OL,6,F"So do the right thing for your former
OL,7,Femployees. You can afford to do it,
OL,8,Fand it's morally right that you do
OL,9,Fthat."
OL,11,FJane agrees, "I think they should be
OL,12,Fstepping up to the plate and paying
OL,13,Fdiscretionary increases and HP choose
OL,14,Fnot to pay it."
OL,16,FA spokesman for Hewlett Packard
OL,17,FEnterprise said, "HPE is committed to
OL,18,Fsatisfying all of its responsibilities
OL,19,Fto both current and former team
OL,20,Fmembers.
